From 47ad7a1d68f7eb1b8bf2019b33f13a74a06e05fb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: quivent <quivent@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 14:05:48 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat(speculative): add MTP single-model speculative decoding

Adds a new common_speculative_mtp_* helper API alongside the existing
common_speculative_* infrastructure. Unlike the standard path which
assumes a separate draft model, the MTP variant sources draft tokens
from a Multi-Token Prediction head on the target context itself, via
the llama_mtp_draft() core-library entry point (owned by the graph
agent; forward-declared here).

Mirrors the MLX reference at ~/mlx-fork/mtp_speculative_decode.py:
draft K tokens, verify via a single K+1-token forward pass, greedy
accept, trim KV on rejection. Stats (draft/accepted/rejected/forward
passes/rollbacks) match the MLX script's output format.

Also adds examples/mtp-speculative/ mirroring examples/speculative/
but single-model. Reuses LLAMA_EXAMPLE_SPECULATIVE so --draft-max
is exposed.

DeltaNet recurrent-state rollback is stubbed with TODO(rollback)
markers for the rollback agent to fill in; for attention-only
layers the llama_memory_seq_rm-based KV trim is already correct.

Build: compiles cleanly; link of llama-mtp-speculative fails on
_llama_mtp_draft until the graph agent merges.
